# Test data naming

Use realistic, domain-specific names for test fixtures. Avoid generic placeholders like `feature_a`, `Feature A`, `item1`, or `test-user-123` unless the test is specifically about those literal values.

Prefer names that reflect how the product actually talks about the thing under test.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const flagA = featureFlagFactory.build({
  key: "feature_a",
  name: "Feature A",
})

// ✅ GOOD
const whatsAppIntegration = featureFlagFactory.build({
  key: "can_integrate_whatsapp",
  name: "WhatsApp Integration",
})
```

Apply the same idea to variable names: `whatsAppIntegration`, not `flagA`; `envoyeWorkspace`, not `workspace1`.
